"""Recreate PX4's vehicle_angular_velocity from raw sensor_gyro_fifo, and retune the
gyro/dgyro filters offline.

Pipeline (reproduces src/modules/sensors/vehicle_angular_velocity/VehicleAngularVelocity.cpp):

  raw int16 --scale--> [notch0] [notch1] [gyro Butterworth, IMU_GYRO_CUTOFF] = filtered gyro
  filtered gyro --d/dt * fs--> [alpha LPF, IMU_DGYRO_CUTOFF]                  = filtered dgyro
  decimate to the logged publish instants (== "same integration rate", ~GYRO_RATEMAX/.. Hz)
  body = R @ (gyro - cal_offset) - ekf_bias(t)   ;   d_body = R @ dgyro

Filter math is copied verbatim from PX4:
  LowPassFilter2p.hpp (2nd-order Butterworth), NotchFilter.hpp (biquad notch),
  AlphaFilter.hpp (1st-order dgyro LPF). Rotation from rotation.{h,cpp} + Gyroscope.cpp.

Usage:
  python3 recreate_angular_velocity.py [LOG.ulg] --config filter_tune.yaml [--start S] [--end S] [--outdir DIR]

Outputs (in ./recreate_av_<logstem>_plots/, each .png with a companion .pkl.gz for show_figure.py):
  recreate_gyro_timeseries.png   recreate_gyro_psd.png
  recreate_dgyro_timeseries.png  recreate_dgyro_psd.png
  recreate_gyro_bode.png         recreate_gyro_nichols.png   (filter transfer functions)
  recreate_match_metrics.txt     recreate_filter_response.txt (dB loss + phase at freqs of interest)
"""

